# Tribunal cron entry for the operator-configured VM (OpenClaw)
#
# Replace the placeholder values below from local machine context before
# installing. Do not commit a real host checkout or account-specific path.
GU_LOG_DIR=/path/to/gu-log
USAGE_MONITOR=/path/to/usage-monitor.sh
TRIBUNAL_LOG_DIR=/path/to/gu-log-logs
#
# Runs the 4-stage Codex/GPT-5.5 tribunal on backlog articles.
#
# Environment requirements:
#   Codex CLI auth     — seed via interactive `codex` login on the VM
#   GU_LOG_DIR         — path to gu-log repo (set below)
#   USAGE_MONITOR      — executable quota monitor path (set below; fail closed if missing)
#   TZ                 — Asia/Taipei for correct quiet-hours logic
#
# Quiet hours are enforced inside tribunal.sh itself
# (weekday 20:00-02:00 TST — script will sleep and resume automatically).
#
# How to install on VM:
#   crontab -e    # add lines below
#
# Run tribunal on the oldest unprocessed article every 6 hours:
# 0 */6 * * * TZ=Asia/Taipei "$GU_LOG_DIR/scripts/tribunal-cron-runner.sh" >> "$TRIBUNAL_LOG_DIR/tribunal.log" 2>&1

# ─── Alternatively: run tribunal.sh directly on a specific file ───
# 30 9 * * 1-5 TZ=Asia/Taipei bash "$GU_LOG_DIR/scripts/tribunal.sh" <filename.mdx> >> "$TRIBUNAL_LOG_DIR/tribunal.log" 2>&1

# ─── GP pipeline invocation (Go binary, canonical as of Phase 4) ──────────
# 0 10 * * 1-5 TZ=Asia/Taipei "$GU_LOG_DIR/tools/gp-pipeline/gp-pipeline" run <tweet_url> >> "$TRIBUNAL_LOG_DIR/gp-pipeline.log" 2>&1
